	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ummmm.&nbsp;&nbsp;No.<br><br>Admittedly, I do not have a high level shaman, but I have to go with Gorthin on this for no other reason than his advice has been spot-on ever since he began posting on this board-- and that has been a LOT longer than any of you, I imagine.  He has the experience of playing a shammy from waaaaaaay back when this game was new, judging from his post dates, and having followed him in his exploits and commented on them extensively myself for many months, I submit to you that when he says 200 WIS is a goal, not a requirement, and that utilizing 50% of his mana pool in any given situation is the reality of shamanistic life in EQ, he knows of what he is speaking.<br>Now, if you wanna talk about high level monkeys, on the other hand, I would be willing to dispense advice as necessary...<br><br>Pusbag Infection, King of the Trolls<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
