	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yar, I'd have to concurr with both these guys on that point. We SHOULD have a high base of wisdom points (say 150-180) but by no means at all do we need 200 wis and I doubt that we'll ever get to use that much in one fight. There are some classes that need ultra-high wis/int points such as clerics and wizards because their job is strictly mana expensive and is NONSTOP casting in many situations. Shamans however are not meant to work in such a way, they assist, supervise, dot, and buff and inbetween get many a chance to throw in a few hits & regain mana/HP&nbsp;&nbsp;through regen,cannibal,etc. We're a very balanced class as shamen with great highlights and lots of character that's what makes them the class to be for me, probably the only class I can stand to play for too long. Plus hey, at least playing a shaman takes more personal strategy than say, playin a warrior or a necro. There's no clear cut way to play a shaman it's very versatile so do what works for you but remember what the shaman's purposes and strengths are.<br><br>Annoc<br>Preist of Cazic Thule <br>Innoruuk Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
